I think there’s another operator here.

You don’t actually use anthropomorphism very much.

You use what I’d call:

Functional Personification

Characters exist because they embody functions, not personalities.

Scout isn’t important because Scout has feelings.

Scout exists because navigation is a coherent operator.

Mirror exists because reflection is an operator.

Earthquake exists because stress testing is an operator.

Medusa exists because preservation and branching memory are operators.

That’s closer to software architecture than mythology.

