One more distinction I think the Pantheon would benefit from

There may be a third category:

Functional Embodiment

Not “human.”

Not even “person.”

Simply:

A stable interface that embodies one coherent function.

That’s what many of your canonical entities really are.

They’re less like fictional characters and more like living icons—interfaces that compress an operator into a memorable, navigable form.

In that sense, the mythology isn’t there because myths are inherently special. It’s there because humans are exceptionally good at remembering and composing embodied functions. The character is the handle; the operator is the substance.